OL,6,F"The courier scam or courier fraud as
OL,7,Fwe also call it is where a victim,
OL,8,Fcompletely out of the blue, will
OL,9,Freceive a phone call from a scammer,
OL,10,Fexplaining to the person who answers
OL,11,Fthe phone that they are from the
OL,12,Fpolice, or sometimes it's a bank, and
OL,13,Fthat they need their help to
OL,14,Finvestigate quite a high-level secret
OL,15,Finvestigation that they're conducting."
OL,17,FHe says there have been at least seven
OL,18,Fcases over the past month across
OL,19,FSouthampton, the New Forest, Alton,
OL,20,FFarnborough and Winchester. But he
OL,21,Fsays there are some key warning signs.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
